                answer: "In the lab frame with stationary target: Total 4-momentum squared is a Lorentz invariant: s = (E_total)² − (p_total c)² = (E_p + m_t c²)² − (p_p c)². Using E_p² − (p_p c)² = (m_p c²)²: s = (m_p c²)² + 2E_p m_t c² + (m_t c²)². Non-relativistically, E_p = m_p c² + T (where T << m_p c²), so: s ≈ (m_p c²)² + 2(m_p c² + T) m_t c² + (m_t c²)² = (m_p c² + m_t c²)² + 2T m_t c². At threshold, products are all at rest in CM frame: s_threshold = (Σm_products c²)². Using Q = (Σm_reactants − Σm_products)c², so Σm_products c² = (m_p + m_t)c² − Q = (m_p + m_t)c² + |Q|. s_threshold ≈ ((m_p + m_t)c² + |Q|)² ≈ (m_p + m_t)²c⁴ + 2|Q|(m_p + m_t)c² (for |Q| << (m_p+m_t)c²). Setting equal: (m_p + m_t)²c⁴ + 2T m_t c² = (m_p + m_t)²c⁴ + 2|Q|(m_p + m_t)c². Simplifying: 2T m_t c² = 2|Q|(m_p + m_t)c² → KE_threshold = T = |Q|(m_p + m_t)/m_t ✓"
