                question: "Germany's Energiewende policy replaced nuclear plants with renewables plus continued gas use during 2011–2022, while France maintained its 70% nuclear grid. Calculate and compare the 2022 electricity carbon intensities of each grid (Germany ≈ 350 gCO₂/kWh in 2022; France ≈ 56 gCO₂/kWh in 2022). What does this imply about the relationship between nuclear, renewables, and decarbonisation speed?",
