                hint: "Convert % to fractions, multiply each by its mass, and sum.",
                answer: "Ar = (34.969 × 0.7577) + (36.966 × 0.2423) = 26.497 + 8.956 = 35.453 u ≈ 35.45 (4 s.f.). This matches the periodic table value of 35.45, confirming the weighted average formula. The non-integer value arises from the mixture of ³⁵Cl (~76%) and ³⁷Cl (~24%) — the Ar value of 35.45 lies between 35 and 37, much closer to 35 because ³⁵Cl is three times more abundant."
