                hint: "Let the fractional abundance of ¹⁰B = x, then ¹¹B = (1 − x). Write the weighted average equation and solve for x.",
                answer: "Let fractional abundance of ¹⁰B = x, so ¹¹B = (1 − x). Weighted average: 10.013x + 11.009(1 − x) = 10.81. 10.013x + 11.009 − 11.009x = 10.81. −0.996x = 10.81 − 11.009 = −0.199. x = 0.199/0.996 = 0.1998 ≈ 0.200. Abundance of ¹⁰B ≈ 20.0%; abundance of ¹¹B ≈ 80.0%. These match the accepted IUPAC values of 19.9% (¹⁰B) and 80.1% (¹¹B) closely, confirming the algebra."
