                answer: "Expected mass = 6 × m_p + 6 × m_n + 6 × m_e = 6(1.00728) + 6(1.00866) + 6(0.000549) = 6.04368 + 6.05196 + 0.003294 = 12.09893 u. Mass defect Δm = 12.09893 − 12.000 = 0.09893 u. Binding energy = Δm × 931.5 MeV/u = 0.09893 × 931.5 = 92.16 MeV. Binding energy per nucleon = 92.16/12 = 7.68 MeV/nucleon — consistent with the accepted value of 7.68 MeV/nucleon for carbon-12. The mass 'missing' from the carbon nucleus is converted to binding energy by E = mc², holding the nucleons together."
