                answer: "Radon production: ²²²Rn is produced in a natural decay chain starting from ²³⁸U in granite, limestone, and other uranium-bearing rocks. The chain is: ²³⁸U → ... → ²²⁶Ra (t₁/₂ = 1600 years) → ²²²Rn (t₁/₂ = 3.82 days). Radon is a noble gas — chemically inert and therefore not bound in the crystal lattice of rocks. As it is produced in rocks and soil, it diffuses freely into any connected air space. Building accumulation: concrete blocks and granite materials contain uranium and produce radon continuously. In a well-ventilated building, radon disperses; in an unventilated basement or poorly sealed house in a granite-rich area, radon can accumulate to high concentrations (UK average ~20 Bq/m³; some Devon/Cornwall homes reach >1000 Bq/m³). Dominance: once inhaled, radon decays in the lungs to short-lived alpha-emitting daughters (²¹⁸Po, ²¹⁴Po) that deposit their alpha energy directly in lung tissue — causing significantly more biological damage per unit energy than external gamma radiation. This internal exposure to alpha emitters in the respiratory tract makes radon the largest single source of natural radiation dose and the second leading cause of lung cancer in the UK after smoking."
