        aim: "The aim of the investigations that led to the ionisation smoke detector was to exploit the ionisation of air by alpha radiation to create a sensitive, low-power electronic switch that could detect the interruption of ion current caused by smoke particles entering a measuring chamber — providing early warning of fires at low cost and without requiring an external power source for the detector element.",

        subject: "The subject of the ionisation smoke detector investigations was the current-voltage characteristics of a small ionisation chamber containing an alpha-emitting source — specifically how the steady ionisation current (created by alpha particles ionising air between two electrodes) is altered when smoke particles enter the chamber and attach to the ions, reducing the current and triggering an alarm circuit.",

