        modernConnection: "The phasor addition method is directly verified in the laboratory by comparing theoretical predictions of resultant intensity — calculated from phasor diagrams with known phase differences — against measured intensities in microwave or optical interference experiments. The investigation below uses a simulation or spreadsheet tool to calculate I_R = 4I₀·cos²(φ/2) for a range of phase differences, then compares predictions to experimentally measured intensity values from a two-source microwave or optical setup."
