                answer: "y_total = A·sin(2πf₁t) + A·sin(2πf₂t). Using the identity sin P + sin Q = 2·cos((P−Q)/2)·sin((P+Q)/2): y_total = 2A·cos(2π·(f₁−f₂)t/2)·sin(2π·(f₁+f₂)t/2) = 2A·cos(π(f₁−f₂)t)·sin(π(f₁+f₂)t). This is a sinusoidal wave at the average frequency (f₁+f₂)/2, whose amplitude varies as |2A·cos(π(f₁−f₂)t)|. The amplitude is maximum when cos(π(f₁−f₂)t) = ±1, i.e. when π(f₁−f₂)t = 0, π, 2π... The interval between consecutive maxima is T_beat = 1/|f₁−f₂|, so the beat frequency = |f₁ − f₂|."
