                answer: "Tightening the string increases its tension, which raises the frequency of vibration (f ∝ √T). If the beat frequency increased from 4 to 6 Hz, and the frequency is now higher, the instrument note moved further from 440 Hz. Initially: |f_instrument − 440| = 4, so f_instrument = 436 or 444 Hz. After tightening, f_instrument rose. If it was 436 Hz: raising it would bring it closer to 440, reducing beats (not matching observation). If it was 444 Hz: raising it further from 440 gives more beats (consistent with observation). Therefore the instrument string was at 444 Hz and is now at 446 Hz — it should be loosened to reach 440 Hz."
