                "Different waveform shapes reflect different harmonic spectra — confirming timbre is determined by harmonics",
                "Guitar shows strong 2nd–5th harmonics; flute shows mainly the fundamental with weak overtones",
                "Tuning fork spectrum is nearly pure sinusoidal — only fundamental detectable",
