        modernConnection: "The investigation below uses a modern diffraction grating (typically 300–600 lines/mm) to measure the wavelength of a red laser pointer by measuring the angular positions of first and second-order diffraction maxima and applying the grating equation nλ = d sin(θ) — the same equation Fraunhofer derived two centuries ago."
