        subjectDefinition: "A node is a point or line in a standing wave pattern that remains permanently at zero displacement at all times. An antinode is a point or line where the amplitude of oscillation is maximum — the material undergoes maximum displacement during each cycle. In a standing wave on a string, nodes occur at fixed positions where incident and reflected waves always cancel (destructive superposition), and antinodes are midway between nodes where the waves always reinforce (constructive superposition). Identifying their positions experimentally allows the wavelength, mode shape, and wave speed to be determined.",

