                answer: "For a string resonating in n loops at frequency f: f = nv/(2L) = n/(2L) × √(T/μ). Rearranging for T: √(T/μ) = 2Lf/n → T/μ = (2Lf/n)² = 4L²f²/n². Therefore T = 4L²f²μ/n², which gives n²T = 4L²f²μ. Since L, f, and μ are all constant throughout the experiment, n²T = constant. The constant has the value 4L²f²μ, which can be predicted from known quantities and compared to experimental measurements as a consistency check."
