    aim: "The aim of Braun's development was to create an instrument that could directly visualise rapidly oscillating electrical signals, making it possible to observe waveforms, measure amplitudes and frequencies, and detect phase relationships — measurements that were previously impossible with galvanometers or other deflection-based instruments that could not respond quickly enough to follow oscillating signals.",

