                answer: "T₁ = 20 + 273 = 293 K; T₂ = 80 + 273 = 353 K. V₁/T₁ = V₂/T₂ → V₂ = V₁ × (T₂/T₁) = 45 × (353/293) = 45 × 1.205 ≈ 54.2 mm. The gas column expands from 45 mm to approximately 54 mm when heated from 20°C to 80°C — illustrating that gas volume increases with absolute temperature at constant pressure."
