                "Isochoric process traces a vertical line on the PV diagram — confirming ΔV = 0, no PdV work",
                "Isobaric process traces a horizontal line — work W = PΔV is the area of the rectangle under the line",
                "Isothermal process traces a hyperbola — PV = constant at each point, confirming ideal gas isothermal behaviour",
                "Work done in isochoric process = 0; isobaric work = P × ΔV; isothermal work = area under hyperbola (greatest for same ΔV)",
