        hypothesis: "If thermal conductivity determines the rate of heat flow along a rod, then the rod with the highest thermal conductivity will melt wax beads furthest from the heat source in a given time, and the order of bead-melting distances will match the known order of thermal conductivities of the metals tested",
        purpose: "Compare the thermal conductivity of at least three metals (copper, aluminium, steel) by measuring the distance along each rod at which wax beads melt after a fixed heating time, and rank the materials by relative thermal conductivity — comparing to tabulated values",
