            "Electronics transient analysis: calculating how quickly a power chip heats up after a power surge uses τ = mc_p/(hA) to predict peak temperature",
            "Food science: predicting cooling times for food products (e.g. blast chilling to < 5°C within 90 minutes) uses lumped capacitance for small items where Bi < 0.1",
