        subjectDefinition: "Thermal equilibrium is the state reached when two or more bodies in thermal contact have equalised their temperatures — heat flows from the hotter body to the cooler body until no further net transfer occurs. Calorimetry is the experimental measurement of heat exchange, typically using the principle of conservation of energy: heat lost by the hot body = heat gained by the cold body, expressed as m₁c₁(T₁ − T_f) = m₂c₂(T_f − T₂), where T_f is the final equilibrium temperature.",

