                answer: "Using molar volume: V_m at 25°C = RT/P = 8.314 × 298 / 101,000 = 0.02451 m³/mol = 24.5 L/mol. V = n × V_m = 0.5 × 24.5 = 12.25 L. Verification using PV = nRT: V = nRT/P = 0.5 × 8.314 × 298 / 101,000 = 1238.9/101,000 = 0.01227 m³ = 12.27 L. Both methods give approximately 12.25–12.27 L. Note that both oxygen and nitrogen and helium would all occupy the same 12.25 L for 0.5 mol at these conditions — this is Avogadro's Law: equal moles → equal volumes at same T and P, regardless of gas type."
