        introduction: "Between 1801 and 1802, the English chemist John Dalton published his law of partial pressures, based on experiments in which he mixed different gases in a vessel and measured the resulting total pressure — finding that each gas contributed to the total pressure independently, as though the other gases were absent.",

        aim: "The aim of Dalton's investigation was to determine whether gases in a mixture exert pressure independently of one another, and to derive a law relating the total pressure of a gas mixture to the individual pressures of its components.",

