        subjectDefinition: "Gas pressure arises from the momentum transferred to container walls by colliding gas molecules. Each molecule rebounds elastically from a wall, transferring momentum Δp = 2mv (where m is mass and v is the component of velocity perpendicular to the wall). The pressure P = F/A = (number of collisions per unit area per unit time) × (momentum per collision) = (1/3)(N/V) × m × ⟨v²⟩ = (1/3)ρ⟨v²⟩. This derivation shows that PV = (1/3)Nm⟨v²⟩ — and since average kinetic energy ½m⟨v²⟩ ∝ T, this recovers the ideal gas law. The ping-pong ball model makes this abstract derivation tangible and observable.",

